  <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">FAQ: Content Agency Websites That Convert</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should content agencies show full writing samples or just excerpts?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Show excerpts with links to full pieces. Homepage: scrollable gallery with first 2-3 paragraphs visible, client industry, results ("300% traffic increase"). Each excerpt links to full case study page with complete piece, strategy, execution, results. Why? Marketing managers browse quickly. Excerpt = quick quality check. Full piece = deep dive if interested. ContentCraft: excerpts on homepage increased click-through to full case studies 423%. Full pieces hidden = no clicks. Excerpts visible = they read, click through, hire you.</p>
